  <span id="freeText2353567170219783044" style="display:none">I can't believe Lenin described woke capitalism (and the liberal side of breadtube) in the <a href="https://www.marxists.org/archive/lenin/works/1917/staterev/ch01.htm" rel="nofollow noopener">first paragraph</a> of this text — that those in power will appropriate radical sentiments whilst voiding them of all revolutionary power (check out Marx's <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/189645.The_Eighteenth_Brumaire_of_Louis_Bonaparte" rel="nofollow noopener">Eighteenth Brumaire</a> and Machiavelli's <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/28862.The_Prince" rel="nofollow noopener">Prince</a> for earlier articulations of this). Turns out those militant Trotskyites were right — I should have read the classics.</span>
