        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer163104481" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14139995860854583400">Lenin&apos;s books are not worth reading. Calling upon people to destroy the state is easy enough; building up something after that, not so easy. Claiming that people will magically fall in love with laboring for others doesn&apos;t actually solve the problem, even if Marx (the great prophet) declared it so. <br/><br/>Also, I can&apos;t help but mock the &quot;scientific&quot; nature of Lenin&apos;s plans. As we all know, Russia was indeed ripe for communism. If only we could all live in a world as good as the Soviet Union! Oh, wait..</span>
  <span id="freeText14139995860854583400" style="display:none">Lenin's books are not worth reading. Calling upon people to destroy the state is easy enough; building up something after that, not so easy. Claiming that people will magically fall in love with laboring for others doesn't actually solve the problem, even if Marx (the great prophet) declared it so. <br /><br />Also, I can't help but mock the "scientific" nature of Lenin's plans. As we all know, Russia was indeed ripe for communism. If only we could all live in a world as good as the Soviet Union! Oh, wait...<br /><br />What's that you say, classical liberals? Those who lead the revolution will be reluctant to give up their absolute power? No way! </span>
