  <span id="freeText10018399153367539590" style="display:none">Lenin's writing is incisive and lucid, and his elucidation of numerous passages written by Marx and Engels proves to be immensely useful for fleshing out Marx and Engels' key teachings on the state (and several other facets of Marxism) in a relatively digestible manner</span>
